                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12756551" author="davemssavage" created="Thu, 17 Sep 2009 13:59:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Note the obr repository has been updated so that it now doesn&apos;t cache file urls - it just reuses the existing artifact. Should still remove the hardcoded timeout though.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should be able to use the obr &amp;lt;repository lastmodified=&apos;20090914041009.068&apos; tag to test if the repo is up to date - however might need to do some work with buffered streams, as current parser is implemented as SAX..., or of course could change parsing logic to STaX to allow for early break out if repo is up to date?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12757023" author="db82407" created="Fri, 18 Sep 2009 07:15:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;main problem is already resolved, by previous refactoring of repo cache.&lt;br/&gt;
this issue is now just reminder to remove hard-coded 7-day expiry.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12761893" author="davemssavage" created="Sat, 3 Oct 2009 14:36:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;mark fix versions to allow tracking of project progress&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12893555" author="davemssavage" created="Thu, 29 Jul 2010 08:50:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;partial fix added - updatePeriod is now at least configurable will raise new issue for improvement to lastmodified/url connection timestamp&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
